  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Courier Rider",
  "description": "<p><strong>Essential Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Follows an assigned, daily route or non-routine schedules for the safe transportation of laboratory specimens from client facilities to the laboratory and observing all traffic laws & safety at all times.</li><li>Accords timely collection of specimens and delivery of laboratory reports to customers.</li><li>Packs supplies ordered by customers.</li><li>Prepares ice packs in specimen collection bags and ensure specimens are maintained within allowable temperature.</li><li>Observe biohazard and safety guidelines.</li><li>Ensure the proper maintenance and repairs of motor vehicle to avoid downtime incidence that may affect the timely delibery of Eurofins services.</li><li>Accords an efficient time-management schedule in performing all routes.</li><li>Diligent sorting and distribution of laboratory reports to ensure timely deliveries.</li><li>Adopt proper documentation procedures in the discharge of your duties.</li><li>Observe PDPA guidelines to ensure the accurate sorting and delviery of laboratory reports by self and courier team of any company documents/materials that contain personal data.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Qualifications: GCE ‘O’ Level, or equivalent.</li><li>Familiar with Singapore roads and routes assigned.</li><li>Service and customer oriented</li><li>Proficiency in English.</li><li>Relevant work experience in a hospital laboratory is an added advantage.</li><li>Own a motorcycle.</li></ul>",
